b'' b'|' b'| i have an applicationshell which uses a colormap created with' b'| xcreatecolormap() and uses all of the colors available for my 8-bit' b'| display....when i popup a dialogshell to prompt the user for' b'| some input i want the xmndialogstyle to be set to' b'| xmdialog_primary_application_modal. the result is that if my cursor is' b'| over the dialogshell i get my colormap, but if the cursor is over the' b'| applicationshell (or any window other than the dialogshell) i get the' b"| default colormap. but i'd like it so that if my cursor is over _any_" b'| window of my application, i get my colormap.' b'' b'i *think* this is correct behavior. remember the default' b'colormapfocuspolicy is keyboard (meaning the cmap focus follows the' b"keyboard focus). since the dialog is modal, mwm won't allow keyboard" b"focus onto your main shell, and so it won't allow cmap focus either." b'' b'since it sounds as though you have keyboardfocuspolicy:pointer, i' b'suggest you set colormapfocuspolicy:pointer also. that way, the cmap' b"focus won't slavishly follow keyboard focus, but will beat its own path." b'' b'(if you have keyboardfocuspolicy: explicit, you can set cmap focus' b'explicit also, but you then need a binding to f.focus_color, probably on' b'mb1).' b'--' b'open software foundation\t\t\tuunet!osf.org!dbrooks' b'showres soote my foote' b'' 